Soyuz -LRB- Сою́з -LSB- sɐˈjʉs -RSB- , `` Union '' , as in Сове́тский Сою́з , `` Sovetskiy Soyuz '' , `` Soviet Union '' -RRB- is a series of spacecraft designed for the Soviet space programme by the Korolyov Design Bureau -LRB- now RKK Energia -RRB- in the 1960s that remains in service today .
The Soyuz succeeded the Voskhod spacecraft and was originally built as part of the Soviet manned lunar programs .
The Soyuz spacecraft is launched on a Soyuz rocket , the most frequently used and most reliable launch vehicle in the world to date .
The Soyuz rocket design is based on the Vostok launcher , which in turn was based on the 8K74 or R-7A Semyorka , a Soviet intercontinental ballistic missile .
All Soyuz spacecraft are launched from the Baikonur Cosmodrome in Kazakhstan .